# ElastiCache — Redis vs. Memcached

## Redis (+ Valkey) — the default

- Rich **data structures** (sorted sets, streams, geo…)
- **Persistence**, **replication + Multi-AZ failover**, **cluster sharding** (≤ 500)
- Pub/sub, Lua, transactions, backup · mostly **single-threaded**

## Memcached — simple only

- **Strings only**; **no** persistence / replication / failover
- **Multi-threaded** (scales with cores), node-add scaling

**Default = Redis.** Memcached only for simple K/V where multi-thread throughput matters + node loss is fine.

## The tier stacks (not replaces)

Source of truth → **RDS / Aurora** · pool → **RDS Proxy** (Lambda) · read scale → replicas then **ElastiCache** · sub-ms (sessions, counters, leaderboards) → **ElastiCache**.
